To add a new plugin:

  git submodule add <repository>

To update after a fresh checkout:

  git submodule init
  git submodule update

To update all plugins to the latest version:

  git submodule update --remote --merge

Current list:

  command-t               file navigation via <Leader>t       *
    to compile extension: cd command-t/ruby/command-t; ruby extconf.rb; make
  IndentConsistencyCop    check indentation consistency
  jedi-vim                Python autocompletion
    in jedi-vim run: git submodule update --init
  syntastic               syntax checking plugin              *
  taglist.vim             show source code structure          *
  vimagit                 single buffer Git plugin
  vim-fireplace           Clojure REPL support
  vim-gitgutter           show git diff in the sign column    *
  vim-javascript          improved Javascript indentation and syntax support *
  vim-preview             preview markup files                +
  vim-salve               support for Leiningen
    dependencies: vim-projectionist, vim-dispatch
  vim-solidity            syntax support for Solidity
  vim-surround            surround things with parentheses/quotes/etc. *
  vimtips-fortune         show tips on startup
  supertab                allow autocompletion via tab key    *
  vim-latex-live-preview  live preview for latex files        *
  vim-go                  Go development plugin               *

  * via NixOS
  + needs gem: nix-shell -p stdenv; gem install --user-install redcarpet
